🔥 **PostgreSQL High Availability: Building a Self-Healing PostgreSQL 17 Cluster (Step-by-Step)**

Most database outages don’t happen because of bugs.
They happen because **failover and recovery weren’t automated.**

Recently I built a **production-ready PostgreSQL HA cluster** using:

• PostgreSQL 17
• TimescaleDB
• repmgr
• Keepalived
• VIP based failover + automatic node recovery

Goal of this architecture:

✅ Automatic failover
✅ Zero application connection change (VIP)
✅ Automatic failed node rejoin
✅ Fully automated cluster recovery

---

# 🏗 Architecture

```
Client Applications
        |
   Virtual IP (VIP)
     Keepalived
        |
----------------------------
|                          |
TIMESCALEDBM01         TIMESCALEDBM02
   PRIMARY                STANDBY
 PostgreSQL 17          PostgreSQL 17
  TimescaleDB            TimescaleDB
    repmgrd               repmgrd
        \                  /
         ---- WAL STREAM ---
```

Applications connect only to the **VIP**, so failover is transparent.

